	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Tutorial room</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From The Cataclysm: Dark Days Ahead Wiki</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><br />
</p>
<table class="infobox" cellspacing="5" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em; width: 150px;">
<caption>
</caption>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="" colspan="2" style="font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; text-align:center;"><span style="font: 1em FixedSys, monospace; color:darkcyan; background:black;">O</span> tutorial room
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th style="">See Cost
</th>
<td class="" style="width: 70%;">5
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>The tutorial room is the room where the tutorial takes place. The Tutorial of C:DDA spawns you into the Tutorial Room, which is square in the middle of a large lake (or very rarely on land), as "John Smith". The tutorial world is different from regular worlds in that the world starts at day 1 (spring season), so expect low temperatures, and you can't customize your character - you're stuck with a blank slate.
</p><p>John Smith starts with 5 melee, 5 marksmanship, no clothing, a lighter (which will tumble to the floor since he starts with no storage), and the Quick trait. With a 0 swimming skill, you won't be able to carry much out given the lake.
</p><p>Many actions performed in the tutorial world will produce an information box at the top of the screen, providing useful information to a new player. As of 0.E-3 and probably earlier, the info boxes may not appear when their requirements are met and sometimes appear without meeting the requirements.
</p><p>The tutorial room has a section above ground and below ground. The above and below are split into two halves: top and bottom, by a wall with 6 doors and 3 curtained windows.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
